The word θερίζειν is rather more common for reaping and harvesting‚ and is given as a synonym of ἀμᾶν by Hesych. Both are used alike of the reaping of corn (ἀμ. in Lev. XXV, 11, Deut. xxiv, 19, Isa. xvii. 5) and the mowing of grass (θερ. in Ps. cxxix. 7). Both are used also in a metaphorica] sense of cutting sheer off, as in Hes. leeoy. 181 (of Oronos mutilating his father) ἤμησε, Soph. Aj. 239 (of Ajax) γλῶσσαν ῥίπτει θερίσας.
